reviewText: My memories of WCW continue here at WCW Uncensored.  It was around this time that WCW reunited both versions of nWo and made the the red & black "Wolfpac" version the "A" team while the "Hollywood/Black & White" version of the nWo was the "B" team (if that makes any sense).  Ric Flair is currently the President of WCW but had his son, David Flair, turn his back on him & cost him his shot at the WCW Title at the last PPV.WCW Crusierweight Champion Billy Kidman vs. Mikey Whipwreck - For those who don't already know about him, he is an ECW original & the first man to hold all 3 championships in ECW.  This was Mikey's debut & his best match during his short WCW run as him & Kidman had an outstanding opening match with many high flyin' moves with a fast pace.And as a side note by reading some of these other reviews, Mikey Whipwreck was not fired a week later as he had several opening/undercard matches in WCW including one with Van Hammer at the Great American Bash 3 months later.  He was released in the fall along with a majority of other unimportant WCW talents as a cost cutting measure.Harlem Street Fight Match: Stevie Ray vs. Vincent - These two were fighting over who was the leader of the "black & white" nWo and quite frankly, was a poor street fight as Vincent just has never been good in the ring while Stevie Ray isn't good enough to carry someone to a decent match.  That didn't solve anything as Horace Hogan threw the slapjack in the middle of the ring & walked off staying "I'm the leader" before Stevie Ray got the victory.Rey Mysterio vs. Kevin Nash - In a tag match last month involving Nash, Mysterio lost & had to unmask.  From there, he became a "giant killer" by pulling out upset wins over other big men like Nash, Bigelow, Scott Norton building up to this match.  However, this match just made the previous weeks of buildup for Rey seem like a waste as the "bigger" Nash easily got the win over the "smaller" Rey in short time.Jerry Flynn vs. Sonny Ono & The Cat - Long & boring filler, skip.Hardcore Match: Raven vs. Bam Bam Bigelow vs. Hak - This was the beginning stages of WCW starting to incorporate a hardcore division and they kicked it off with 3 former ECW Champions.  This was one of WCW's best hardcore matches as you just has a "New Jack" weaponsfest featuring mailboxes, tables, steel chairs, canes, boat paddles, fire extinguishers, fans, an ironing-board and others "plunder" as Dusty Rhodes likes to say.  This was a fun match to watch as you can't help but laugh & think "ouch" at some of the spots that didn't go off as planned.Lumberjack Match: WCW Tag Team Champions Curt Hennig & Barry Windham vs. Chris Benoit & Dean Malenko - This was a rematch from last month's tag team tournament finals.  To play off the fact that Windham used a leather belt to get the victory last month, the lumberjacks have straps.  Unfortunally, my VHS tape was real dirty around this match so I can't really comment here but I remember it was a solid match.Dog Collar Match: Perry Saturn vs. Chris Jericho - This feud was built around Jericho embarrising Saturn for months including making him wear a dress as a result of losing a match (think Brian Pillman/Goldust in 1997) but Saturn added his own twist here by going with a goth-like latex look & coming out to generic Marlyn Manson-like theme music.  The match itself was average & nothing special as Jericho added some entertainment value with Ralphus in the beginning & even wearing a mouthpiece throughout the match but for a match that has a history of being violent (remember Piper/Valentine), this was softcore.WCW Television Champion Scott Steiner vs. Booker T - This was a good match (but nothing noteworthy) between the two that went back & forth and showcased why Steiner was a "heat magnet" in WCW when it came to his interaction with the fans.Barbed Wire Steel Caged/First Blood Match: WCW Champion Hollywood Hogan vs. Ric Flair - The added stipulations for this match were that if Ric Flair wins, he will becoming the official WCW President (he was only work as President for 90 days which were coming up soon) but if Hogan wins then Flair must leave wrestling.  This is a match where if you didn't understand the story being told, this match came off real confusing as it was advertised as a "first blood" match but when Flair was the first one to start bleeding, the referee let the match continue showing that he was heavily biased towards Flair in this match.  This cage match was tons better than their cage match at Halloween Havoc '94 but it wasn't their best encounter but an interesting note here was how you started the hear the fans starting to cheer for Hogan despite the fact that he was the leader of the nWo.In the end, Uncensored was an average PPV from WCW that you really aren't missing anything if you don't see it.  I would give this a 2.5 but I'll be nice & round it up to three so I would only recommend at a low price or if your just a huge fan of the WCW product at that time.
summary: Maybe This Should Have Been Censored?

reviewText: By March of 1999, WCW was beginning to go down. While still competing with WWF (not yet WWE), they were not as powerful as they once were with bad booking and business deals behind the scenes.This card was one of the few that was a bright spot. Here it is:Billy Kidman Vs. Mikey Whipwreck (WCW Cruiserweight Title Match) - Mikey had just recently left ECW for WCW and this was one of his first bouts in the organization. Kidman was on a hot streak as WCW Cruiserweight Champion but it would be threatened here as both men gave a great opener! Kidman retains the Cruiserweight title!Vincent Vs. Stevie Ray (Harlem Streetfight for control of nWo Black & White) - The weakest bout on this whole card! Fighting for the nWo Black & White when everyone knew this was a joke! LOL! By the way, Stevie Ray won with his "flapjack" manuvear (his version of The Pedigree).Kevin Nash vs. Rey Mysterio, Jr. - Surprisingly entertaining as Nash and Mysterio (who is unmasked in this one) put on a good bout. Rey doesn't get lucky in this one when Nash (with help from Lex Luger) catches him in his powerbomb for the win.Jerry Flynn Vs. Ernest Miller & Sonny Oono (Handicap Match) - I'll be honest, I don't even remember who won this stinker. I called Vincent/Stevie Ray the worst bout but this one is a close second! Watch once and skip!Bam Bam Bigelow vs. Hardcore Hak (a.k.a. The Sandman) vs. Raven - This match may as well have been in ECW because it was certainly ECW worthy! Ends with a surprise turn of Chasity on Raven, allowing Hardcore Hak to get the win!Curt Hennig & Barry Windham Vs. Chris Benoit & Dean Malenko (WCW World Tag Team Championship under Lumberjack Rules with Straps) - Aside from the Lumberjacks being on the outside with belts, this was actually a great wrestling match with good psychology! It gets wild near the end as Arn Anderson nails Hennig with a tire iron after being cheap shotted by him. Ends when Benoit nails Hennig with his now infamous flying headbutt for the pin and the titles!Chris Jericho vs. Perry Saturn (Dog Collar Match) - In one of his last bouts for WCW, Jericho took on Saturn in a Dog Collar Match! Good suplexes and use of the chain. Ends when Saturn beats Jericho after a Death Valley Driver!Scott Steiner vs. Booker T (WCW World TV Title Match) - Great matchup between these two. Ends when Bagwell's attempt at interference backfires on Scott. Booker would go on to win another TV title. As for Scott and Booker, these two would have an even better bout a month later at Spring Stampede '99 for the WCW U.S. title.Hulk Hogan vs. Ric Flair (WCW World Title Barbed Wire Cage Match) - While an exciting match overall, this one had to be one of the most cluster-f***ed as far as booking! Originally, it was supposed to be under "First Blood" rules but the referee for the bout (Charles Robinson/A known Flair mark) refused to stop the match though Hogan had clearly busted open Flair! Then, when Hogan had him pinned, Robinson refused to count! Basically, it made no freakin' sense! Then again, a lot that WCW did at that time didn't make sense!That being said, this is still a great match between the two. I personally thought their encounter a month earlier at Superbrawl was actually better but this was still a good one. I just wished they would've gotten their booking straight instead of opting for all the confusion.As a whole, this card is worth looking at as it was one of WCW's better cards at that point in time.
summary: One Of WCW's Better Cards During Its Final Years

reviewText: Soak it up Hulkamaniacs or is it NWO-ites...who knows anyway this actually renewed my faith in Hogan for like a 20 hours, until Nitro.  Hogan somehow turned out a babyface performance and Flair well Flair's always good, Hogan loses but its good to see Hogan actually working a match, probably because in the cage you have to be original to get over.  GOOD PPV, one of WCW's few

reviewText: This PPV was a decent WCW event from 1999 which had its good and bad points throughout the night.WCW Cruiserweight TitleBilly Kidman (c) vs. Mikey Whipwreck - This was a very short stint in WCW for Mikey but proves how WCW threw away good talent. This was the match of the night and both steal the show, this was a brilliant match with many good high spots and Kidman and Mikey work excellent together. 9/10Harlem StreetfightVincent vs. Stevie Ray - Crappy brawl which is just a waste of time, basically a filler match. Stevie wins with the flapjack (lifted pedigree) and finishes a poor match. 2/10Rey Mysterio Jr vs. Kevin Nash w/ Lex Luger and Elizabeth - Rey was coming off some huge wins against people like Nash and was getting a big push which is why this match confuses me. Rey has about 3 big moves and then is put away with the Jackknife, this ends the feud between the two quite abruptly and makes Reys other wins seem pointless. 4/10Handicap MatchThe Cat and Sonny Ono vs. Jerry Flynn - Dragged was stupid and the ending looks messed up. 1/10Bam Bam Bigelow vs. Hardcore Hak vs. Raven w/ Chastity - Brilliant hardcore match a copy of the old ECW battles. Lots of weapons, tables and chairs with some good bumps and weapon shots on all three guys. Didnt expect this from WCW and was a good hardcore battle with non stop action. 9/10WCW Tag Team Titles Lumberjack MatchCurt Hennig and Barry Windham (c) vs. Benoit and Malenko - Some people might think this was a excellent technical tag match but i thought it was just dull with some rare good moments. 3/10Dog Collar MatchChris Jericho vs. Perry Saturn - This match is crazy Saturn wrestles in a leather dress! A good battle between the two with some funny moments. 8/10WCW TV TitleScott Steiner (c) w/ Buff Bagwell vs. Booker T - An Ok match but because Scott cant wrestle well he makes Booker look worse, not good but not the worst match either. 5/10WCW Heavyweight Title Barbed Wire Steel Cage MatchHulk Hogan (c) vs. Ric Flair - These two where hogging the lime light at this point and holding guys back. This was a decent match but both have had much better. 7/10
